Indiana Michigan Power Contributions
Dear Friends,
Indiana Michigan Power takes pride in providing dependable, clean and affordable energy to families and businesses throughout Indiana and Michigan. Our commitment doesn’t stop at the light switch.  We are investing in the communities we serve not only through monetary donations, but through volunteerism and community service. 

I&M's giving philosophy emphasizes education, economic development, the environment and enhancing the quality of life for citizens across the 164 communities we serve. Whether it’s building homes for the less fortunate, providing support for children to explore their curiosity for science and technology or assisting senior citizens with yard clean-up, I&M and our 2,400 employees enjoy giving back to the communities where we live and work.

In 2016, I&M contributed nearly $375,000 to non-profit and economic development agencies. In addition, the American Electric Power Foundation contributed more than $300,000 to non-profit agencies in our service territory. 

In this report, you will see a list of some of the agencies that received contributions from Indiana Michigan Power and the American Electric Power Foundation. 

Thank you for the opportunity to serve you and support the people and organizations that make our communities great places to live. 

Sincerely,


Toby Thomas
President and Chief Operating Officer
Indiana Michigan Power
